58th Street (formerly Betts Ave. and also Covert Street, foreground not seen.) at Fifty-sixth Ave. (Note that the 2½ story wing was in line of the last mentioned Ave. The house was not standing in 1929.) The owners of this house were Charles G. Covert from 1860-1873, and Cord Meyer in 1891. It was formerly designated as 246 Betts Ave.

1922.
View 2: March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
